comments: Horford (BOS) brings his hands toward Schroder (LAL) and marginal contact occurs as Horford (BOS) releases away to roll.
Hachimura (LAL) rests his left hand to Brown's (LAL) lower body and marginal contact occurs as he contests the driving shot attempt.
Williams (BOS) initiates illegal contact with Davis (LAL) as he attempts to get to the pass in the post.

Replay review of the foul called on Brogdon (BOS) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Brogdon (BOS) swipes down and makes clean contact with the ball that dislodges it away from Davis (LAL) during his upward shooting motion.
Beverley (LAL) and Tatum (BOS) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Williams (BOS) gives a step of distance when establishing himself in Beverley's (LAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact during the screen.
James (LAL) maintains a rested forearm on Brown's (BOS) side and marginal contact occurs as he contests Brown's shot attempt.
Hachimura (LAL) initiates contact with Brogdon's (BOS) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Davis (LAL) pushes Brown (BOS) into Schroder (LAL) at the start of Schroder's drive.
Brown (BOS) briefly brings both hands into Schroder's (LAL) path and marginal contact occurs during his drive.

Williams (BOS) brushes Beverley's (LAL) head and marginal contact occurs during his put-back attempt. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Williams (BOS) is already in Beverley's (LAL) path and he absorbs the contact during the screen.
Williams (BOS) firms up in Beverley's (LAL) path and both players engage and disengage as the screen is set.
Williams (BOS) commits a take foul on Beverley (LAL).
Beverley (LAL) initiates contact with Brown's (BOS) head during the layup attempt.
Tatum (BOS) initiates contact with James' (LAL) arm, affecting his shot attempt at the rim.
All Flagrant Fouls are reviewed by League Operations.
Schroder (LAL) establishes himself in Tatum's (BOS) path and does not deliver illegal contact as the pick is set.
Westbrook (LAL) extends both hands forward and initiates contact with Tatum (BOS), affecting his ability to set the pick.
Davis (LAL) legally contests Brown's (BOS) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Horford (BOS) is moving alongside Westbrook's (LAL) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Schroder (LAL) brings both hands forward to Brown's (BOS) path, and marginal contact occurs as he is able to maintain his dribble during the drive.
Horford (BOS) maintains verticality and absorbs the oncoming contact that occurs during James' (LAL) driving shot attempt.
Westbrook (LAL) moves into Brown's (BOS) path and initiates body contact that affects his driving shot attempt.
Kornet (BOS) lightly brushes Schroder's (LAL) arm and marginal contact occurs during Schroder's driving shot attempt.
Schroder (LAL) reaches in and makes clean contact with the ball that dislodges it away from Tatum (BOS).
Westbrook (LAL) commits a take foul on Brogdon (BOS).
Beverley (LAL) commits a take foul on Tatum (BOS).
